-- Kenyan Lawmakers Approve 30% Pay Increase, Higher Allowances, Nation Says
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-07-01T05:58:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/kenyan-lawmakers-approve-30-pay-increase-higher-allowances-nation-says.html

          
          
             Kenyan lawmakers approved proposals
for a 30 percent pay hike, boosting their monthly salary to 1.1
million shillings ($13,456), the  Daily Nation  reported.  
 Legislators also backed proposals to increase allowances
for attending parliamentary sessions, the Nairobi-based
newspaper said, citing a report by an independent salary review
panel that also suggested lawmakers pay higher income taxes.  
